Quote:  I was amused to hear in the radio lunch-time Country Session a reference to `fruit-salad breed' as a possible cause of the undesirable hairiness in slipe wool. I wonder is this another New Zealand-ism for the appendix to the Dictionary? [not Griffiths handwriting]
